episodes.title: The Mook, the Chef, the Wife and Her Homer
episodes.plot: When Fat Tony has to take a time-out due to a whacking attempt, Homer and Bart take over the business.

episodes.title: Jazzy & The Pussycats
episodes.plot: Lisa becomes depressed when Bart becomes a better jazz musician than her. So she decides to set up an animal shelter in the Simpsons' attic.

episodes.title: Please Homer, Don't Hammer 'Em
episodes.plot: Marge begins her own carpentry business, but Homer becomes the face of the business because nobody will take a female carpenter seriously. And Bart uses Principal Skinner's peanut allergy to his advantage.

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror XVII
episodes.plot: A meteorite turns Homer into a rampaging blob with a voracious appetite; Bart brings a Golem to life; an alien invasion hoax turns real.

episodes.title: G.I. (Annoyed Grunt)
episodes.plot: Homer is duped into signing up for the Army, and his hijinks after basic training ultimately results in a military occupation of Springfield.

episodes.title: Moe'N'a Lisa
episodes.plot: Lisa helps Moe become a distinguished poet, but she turns on him when he takes all the credit for his newfound greatness.

episodes.title: Ice Cream of Margie (with the Light Blue Hair)
episodes.plot: Homer becomes an ice cream man after being fired from the plant, and Marge uses his leftover Popsicle sticks to create folk art figures.

episodes.title: The Haw-Hawed Couple
episodes.plot: Bart and Nelson become best friends, but Bart surprisingly discovers that the fringe benefits aren't worth Nelson's neediness.

episodes.title: Kill Gil, Vol. 1 & 2
episodes.plot: The Simpsons let Gil stay with them during Christmas. However, he stays for 11 months because Marge can't tell him "no."

episodes.title: The Wife Aquatic
episodes.plot: Homer returns Marge to Barnacle Bay, where she spent her beloved summer vacations. But when they get there, they discover that it is no longer a tourist spot.

episodes.title: Revenge Is a Dish Best Served Three Times
episodes.plot: While Homer tries to get revenge on a driver who cut him off, his family warns him of the folly of revenge by telling stories based on "The Count of Monte Cristo," "Revenge of the Nerds," and "Batman."

episodes.title: Little Big Girl
episodes.plot: Lisa embellishes her family heritage as Native American for a school project; Bart gets a driver's license and develops a relationship with an older girl.

episodes.title: Springfield Up
episodes.plot: A parody of the "Up Series" of British documentaries, in which a filmmaker follows Homer and his friends from grade school into their 40s.

episodes.title: Yokel Chords
episodes.plot: In this parody of The Sound of Music (1965), Lisa becomes a tutor for Cletus' seven children, until Krusty tries to exploit them as entertainers. Meanwhile, Bart becomes emotionally attached to his school-appointed psychiatrist.

episodes.title: Rome-old and Juli-eh
episodes.plot: Selma and Grampa fall in love and end up getting married, a marriage both Homer and Patty are against.

episodes.title: Homerazzi
episodes.plot: Homer becomes a successful Paparazzi, but Springfield's celebrities decide to get their revenge on him.

episodes.title: Marge Gamer
episodes.plot: Marge decides to find out what their Internet has to offer and soon gets hooked on an online role-playing game; Homer referees Lisa's soccer game.

episodes.title: The Boys of Bummer
episodes.plot: Bart becomes the most hated person in Springfield after he is the goat in a championship baseball game, and Homer's new job as a mattress salesman ruins his and Marge's sex life.

episodes.title: Crook and Ladder
episodes.plot: Homer, Moe, Apu and Principal Skinner become volunteer firefighters. But just because they're not getting paid doesn't mean that they can't find a way to receive compensation.

episodes.title: Stop, or My Dog Will Shoot!
episodes.plot: Homer unwittingly drags the family into a cornfield maze after attempting to leave a boring Harvest fest that Marge brought them to. When everyone except Homer escapes, Santa's Little Helper rescues him and becomes the town hero. So the Simpsons enroll him in Police Dog Academy where he's teamed with Lou.

episodes.title: 24 Minutes
episodes.plot: Bart and Lisa join forces to stop the school bullies from setting off a stink bomb at the school bake sale.

episodes.title: You Kent Always Say What You Want
episodes.plot: After Kent Brockman is fired as a news anchor, he and Lisa use the Internet to expose the Fox News Conspiracy.
